# ðŸ“Œ INSTRUCTIONS:
# Open this file in Vim and try the commands listed below.
# Each task includes the correct Vim command to help you learn.
# copy the /etc/passwd file to a new file named /passwdbackup      
  open the /passwdbackup file and perform all the task 
# ðŸ”¹ TASK 1: MOVEMENT
# ------------------------------
# 1. Move to the top of the file         --> Vim Command: gg
# 2. Move to the bottom of the file      --> Vim Command: G
# 3. Move to the end of the line         --> Vim Command: $
# 4. Move to the beginning of the line   --> Vim Command: ^
# 5. Jump to line 20                     --> Vim Command: :20

# ðŸ”¹ TASK 2: INSERTING TEXT
# ------------------------------
# 6. Insert your name at the top         --> Vim Command: gg then O
# 7. Add a new line after line 10        --> Vim Command: :10 then o
# 8. Append " - Practice Complete"       --> Vim Command: A then type the text

# ðŸ”¹ TASK 3: DELETING TEXT
# ------------------------------
# 9. Delete a line                       --> Vim Command: dd
# 10. Delete first word on next line     --> Vim Command: dw

# ðŸ”¹ TASK 4: COPYING & PASTING
# ------------------------------
# 11. Yank line 15                       --> Vim Command: :15 then yy
# 12. Paste it below                     --> Vim Command: p
# 13. Paste it above                     --> Vim Command: P

# ðŸ”¹ TASK 5: SEARCH & REPLACE
# ------------------------------
# 14. Search for "TASK"                  --> Vim Command: /TASK
# 15. Replace "TASK" with "CHALLENGE"    --> Vim Command: :%s/TASK/CHALLENGE/g

# ðŸ”¹ TASK 6: UNDO, REDO, SAVE & EXIT
# ------------------------------
# 16. Undo last change                   --> Vim Command: u
# 17. Redo change                        --> Vim Command: Ctrl + r
# 18. Save the file                      --> Vim Command: :w
# 19. Quit Vim                           --> Vim Command: :q
# 20. Save and quit                      --> Vim Command: :wq

# âœ… BONUS:
# ------------------------------
# 21. Macro to insert "[âœ“]" at start
#     Vim Command:
#       qa          # Start recording
#       I[âœ“] <Esc>  # Insert text at start
#       q           # Stop recording
#       @a          # Play macro once
#       10@a        # Play 10 times

# ðŸŽ‰ Great job! Keep practicing until it's muscle memory!
# ==============================
